sec.p:
In most cellular networks there are two types of APNs: the usual WAP APN, enabling access to the default WAP content (or the operator's
walled garden
) and a second type, known as Internet or WEB APN, which enables access to all content. The WAP APN normally filters non-WAP content by traffic, ports or volume. The Internet/Web APN is normally unfiltered and often the operator will charge a higher tariff for it. Handhelds, laptops and smartphones normally need to use the Internet/Web APN when using applications or HTML browsers.
